            <abstract>
                <p>
                    This homily traditionally opens the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1297Dersan">Dǝrsāna Rufāʾel</ref>, but in at least one case 
                    (<ref type="mss" corresp="BNFabb193"/>) it can be found as an independent text.
                    The attribution of a homily on the archangel Raphael to John Chrysostom is already found in the Arabic tradition, whereas there is no trace of it in the European tradition.
                </p>
